\newlabel{sec:mitig:norm@cref}{{[subsection][2][7]\mbox  {VII-B}}{[1][10][]10}}
\@writefile{toc}{\contentsline {paragraph}{\numberline {\mbox  {VII-B}0a}Finding: Correcting RC0 with two optimizations (each necessary, neither sufficient alone) brings TileLang LayerNorm to $124\%$ and RMSNorm to $990\%$ of PyTorch throughput on the A100-SXM4--- a $1347\times $ and $1157\times $ reduction over the unoptimized TileLang baseline (\cref  {tab:norm}): (1) replacing \texttt  {T.serial} reduction loops with the native \texttt  {T.reduce} primitive (the dominant step; in the RTX 4000 Ada optimization campaign this change alone gave $208\times $); (2) switching to native bfloat16/float16 I/O and eliminating intermediate \texttt  {.float()} precision casts. These results confirm RC0 as the primary cause of TileLang's normalization deficit and as fully correctable in user space.}{10}{paragraph.7.2.0.1}\protected@file@percent }
\citation{zhou2021implicit}
